  "sourceCode": "Employer Portal",
  "title": "Accountant",
  "description": "<p><strong>ROLE & RESPONSIBILITIES:</strong></p><ul><li>Preparation of month end pack and reports to regional finance team</li><li>Preparation of various reports and analysis as required to provide value add assistance to the business</li><li>Data entry to accounting system</li><li>Collaborate cross-functionally with other departments to support operational activities</li><li>Enter payment details into online banking systems after all approvals are obtained as per SOA</li><li>Ensure ongoing compliance with global internal control and US SOX regulations</li><li>Preparation of concert/tour settlements and be on site for concerts/festival under his responsibility</li><li>Placement of shows related insurance</li><li>Project reconciliation</li><li>Prepare and filing of withholding tax, GST and other tax matters</li><li>Ensure the accuracy and timeliness of financial statements in compliance with Singapore Financial Reporting Standards (SFRS) and IFRS</li><li>Assist in office admin matters on ad hoc basis</li><li>Other varied accounts duties to support the team</li></ul><p><strong>BEHAVIOUR:</strong></p><ul><li>Proactive team player with initiative and self-motivation</li><li>Focus on quality and service</li><li>Very focused and adaptable to achieving deadlines</li><li>Independent thinker</li><li>Ability to translate a concept into a plan</li></ul><p><strong>QUALIFICATIONS:</strong></p><ul><li>Bachelor’s degree or higher in accounting and CPD/CPA qualification is preferred</li><li>Minimum of 5 years of experience in an accounting or finance role, including multi-entity experience</li><li>Preferably with Regional Exposure Experiences</li><li>Experience with Xero and Oracle is a plus.</li><li>Detail-oriented, meticulous, and able to perform well under pressure.</li><li><strong>Must be able to wo</strong><u><strong>rk later hours or on multiple weekends</strong></u><strong> (expect up to 50% weekends in a calendar days) on show days</strong></li><li><strong>Please do not apply if you are unable to accommodate the required working hours.</strong></li></ul>",
